description: Export an audience of a specified size after you have generated an audience.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the audience export job.

parameters.name: audienceGenerationJobArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the audience generation job that you want to export.

parameters.name: audienceSize
parameters.description: The size of the generated audience. Must match one of the sizes in the configured audience model. Whether the audience size is defined in absolute terms or as a percentage. You can use the ABSOLUTE  AudienceSize to configure out audience sizes using the count of identifiers in the output. You can use the Percentage  AudienceSize to configure sizes in the range 1-100 percent. Specify an audience size value.

nested_params.name: type
nested_params.description: Whether the audience size is defined in absolute terms or as a percentage. You can use the ABSOLUTE  AudienceSize to configure out audience sizes using the count of identifiers in the output. You can use the Percentage  AudienceSize to configure sizes in the range 1-100 percent.
